        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 27 at 5:20PM EDT until June 27 at 6:15PM EDT by NWS Buffalo NY</headline>
        <description>SVRBUF

The National Weather Service in Buffalo has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Wyoming County in western New York...
Southeastern Erie County in western New York...

* Until 615 PM EDT.

* At 520 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 7 miles north of
Chaffee, or 11 miles southeast of East Aurora, moving east at 25
mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

* Locations impacted include...
Letchworth State Park, Perry, Warsaw, Arcade, Chaffee, Wales
Center, Portageville, Varysburg, Holland, and Sardinia.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Torrential rainfall is occurring with this storm, and may lead to
flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
